text: Liberal Senator Andrew Bragg says “it would be very good news if [Labor] is supporting free trade deals,” but the “testimony that came through to the committee showed that labor’s principle concerns were really red herrings”. Mr Bragg told Sky News he’s “not surprised” Labor will back the most recent free trade deals, and he “very much welcomes it”. “Labor has a terrible record on trade – they inherited the Chinese and the Japanese free trade agreement negotiations from John Howard and they failed to deliver them,” he said. The Liberal Senator said “the biggest problem they have is they don’t seem to generate their own policy ideas”. Image: News Corp Australia
